text: Kyzylorda Province or Kyzylorda Region (, ) is a region in the south of Kazakhstan. The capital of region is the city of Kyzylorda. The population is 833,531 (as of 2023). There are only three cities in this region: Kyzylorda, Aral and Kazalinsk. The region also has the Baikonur Cosmodrome and the city of Baikonur, which were purchased by Russia in an agreement that lasts until 2050. ==References==
